 [ END NOTES & FUTURE EXPLORATIONS ]

 This 256b intro would never have been done without the original 3dfx 
 Voodoo card documentation:
 - http://www.o3one.org/hwdocs/video/voodoo_graphics.pdf
 - https://www.falconfly.de/3dfx.htm
 - http://bitsavers.informatik.uni-stuttgart.de/components/3dfx/

 Now that the 3dfx Voodoo 1 is a proven target for 256b sizecoding, there 
 is plenty of room for future exploration. A major sizecoding dilemma 
 arises here: the combined Unreal Mode switch and bare-metal Voodoo PCI 
 initialization devour over a third of the entire 256-byte limit. One 
 hypothesis is whether writing a pure software triangle rasterizer from 
 scratch might actually cost fewer bytes than waking up the hardware.

 However, the hardware route provides massive benefits that are impossible 
 to match in software at this scale. Once the Voodoo is awake, we get 
 sub-pixel correction to 0.4x0.4 resolution, perspective-corrected texture
 mapping, and blistering fast resolutions up to 800x600 entirely for free.
 The hardware does the heavy lifting, leaving the 256b scene to dream up
 new ways to abuse it.

